## 6. Node ID namespaces are heterogeneous — the how-to's A6 plan is half wrong

Prefix distribution from `nodes.parquet` (totals reconcile exactly to the census):

| label | prefixes |
|---|---|
| `DRG` (16,766) | **CHEMBL 15,477 (92%)**, DRUGBANK 1,227 (7%), RXNORM 62 |
| `DIS` (36,345) | **EFO 11,960**, MONDO 11,724 (**32%**), OBA 10,997, Orphanet 1,637, + 9 long-tail (OTAR 9, DOID 6, OBI 4, NCIT 3, MP 2, PATO 2, OGMS 1) |
| `GEN` (61,306) | ENSG 61,108, NCBIGene 198 |
| `PHE` (19,341) | HP 19,177, meddra 164 |
| `ANA`/`BPO`/`CCO`/`MFN`/`PWY`/`EXP` | UBERON / GO / GO / GO / REACT / MESH — single-prefix |

Formatting is not uniformly CURIE either: `DOID_0050890` uses an underscore where
`MONDO:0005148` uses a colon; `meddra` is lowercase.

**Drugs — the how-to is right.** repoDB carries DrugBank IDs; a direct CURIE join
reaches at most 1,227 of 16,766 nodes. **Standardize on InChIKey**, via
`properties.inchi_key` (already on the node). `properties.struct_id` /
`cd_id` (DrugCentral) are an alternative path worth testing — repoDB also carries
DrugCentral IDs.

**Diseases — the how-to is wrong.** "Standardize on MONDO" assumed MONDO *is* the
disease space. It's 32%. This is an **Open Targets–derived, EFO-backboned** space.
Mapping repoDB's UMLS CUIs → MONDO via OxO would strand two thirds of the graph.

Use `properties.umls_cui` / `concept_ids`, present on `DIS` nodes **regardless of
prefix**. repoDB is UMLS CUIs. This removes the OxO dependency entirely — subject
to coverage (`scripts/a1_keycoverage.py`, run at A6).

