## 7. `DIS` is not a disease-only label — ~30% are not diseases

**OBA = Ontology of Biological Attributes**: traits and measurements (bone
density, LDL level), swept in via Open Targets' GWAS space and labelled `DIS`.
**10,997 of 36,345.**

No drug treats a measurement. Left in the candidate pool they inflate the
denominator and hand the agent ~11K unmatched targets.

**Action:** exclude OBA (and review the long-tail PATO/MP/OBI prefixes, which are
also attribute/organism ontologies) from the candidate disease space at **A7
step 5**, alongside the Broad "already-indicated" exclusion. Report the count.

